## VIFs for Example 2


`car::vif()` throws an error! Why?

. . .

$\text{VIF} = \dfrac{1}{1 - R^2_i}$

:::{.incremental}
- Since $x_1$ and $x_2$ are perfectly correlated, $R^2_i = 1$

- This makes the denominator $1 - R^2_i = 0$

- So, $\text{VIF} = \dfrac{1}{0}$ is undefined
:::

